<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1401]" box="[151,670,150,177]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,670,150,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,670,150,177]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">
Overview of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[304,480,150,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[304,480,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Lysmata vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’s 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[505,670,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">global records</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="207" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1401]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">
Reports of “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[287,389,187,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[287,389,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from the eastern Mediterranean and the extreme western Indo-Pacific should be treated with caution and warrant further investigation. For example, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[803,909,223,248]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[803,909,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Mediterranean Sea (
<collectingCountry box="[1217,1289,222,248]" name="Egypt" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Egypt</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdelsalam, K. M." pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="124 - 131" refId="ref16184" refString="Abdelsalam, K. M. (2018) First record of exotic Lysmatid shrimp Lysmata vittata (Stimpson, 1860) (Decapoda: Caridea: Lysmatidae) from the Egyptian Mediterranean coast. Mediterranean Marine Science, 19 (1), 124 - 131. https: // doi. org / 10.12681 / mms. 15591" type="journal article" year="2018">Abdelsalam 2018</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[231,324,258,284]" name="Djibouti" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[340,481,258,285]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="1 - 347" refId="ref21943" refString="Nobili, G. (1906) Faune carcinologique de la Mer Rouge: Decapodes et Stomatopodes. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, 4, 1 - 347. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10635" type="journal article" year="1906">Nobili 1906</bibRefCitation>
), Persian Gulf (
<bibRefCitation author="Kemp, S." box="[658,795,258,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="81 - 129" refId="ref20693" refString="Kemp, S. (1914) Notes on Crustacea Decapoda in the Indian Museum: V. Hippolytidae. Records of the Indian Museum, 10, 81 - 129." type="journal article" year="1914">Kemp 1914</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ashrafi, H. &amp; Dehghani, A. &amp; Sari, A. &amp; Naderloo, R." box="[807,1023,258,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="521 - 534" refId="ref16950" refString="Ashrafi, H., Dehghani, A., Sari, A. &amp; Naderloo, R. (2020) An updated checklist of caridean shrimps of the Persian Gulf and Gulf of Oman. Zootaxa, 4747 (3), 521 - 534. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4747.3.6" type="journal article" year="2020">
Ashrafi 
<emphasis box="[898,955,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
), and Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[1182,1250,258,284]" name="Oman" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Oman</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Naderloo, R. &amp; Ebrahimnezhad, S. &amp; Sari, A." pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="397 - 412" refId="ref21852" refString="Naderloo, R., Ebrahimnezhad, S. &amp; Sari, A. (2015) Annotated checklist of the decapod crustaceans of the Gulf of Oman, northwestern Indian Ocean. Zootaxa, 4028 (3), 397 - 412. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4028.3.5" type="journal article" year="2015">
Naderloo 
<emphasis box="[1379,1437,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ashrafi, H. &amp; Dehghani, A. &amp; Sari, A. &amp; Naderloo, R." box="[222,442,294,320]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="521 - 534" refId="ref16950" refString="Ashrafi, H., Dehghani, A., Sari, A. &amp; Naderloo, R. (2020) An updated checklist of caridean shrimps of the Persian Gulf and Gulf of Oman. Zootaxa, 4747 (3), 521 - 534. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4747.3.6" type="journal article" year="2020">
Ashrafi 
<emphasis box="[315,374,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
), likely reflect 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[617,703,294,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis box="[617,703,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or different taxonomic entities, as the environmental conditions are far more tropical than currently noted for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[658,760,331,356]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[658,760,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is noteworthy that the coloration pattern and morphology of the individual reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[516,583,367,393]" name="Egypt" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Egypt</collectingCountry>
appear similar to both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[852,938,366,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis box="[852,938,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[997,1013,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L</emphasis>
. sp. AUS2: 1) one-segmented accessory branch; 2) 17–19 carpal segments of second pereopod; 3) 7–9 meral segments of the second pereopod; and dark transvers bands on the pleon (which we presume for 
<emphasis box="[815,831,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L</emphasis>
. sp. AUS2) (
<bibRefCitation author="Abdelsalam, K. M." box="[980,1185,438,464]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="124 - 131" refId="ref16184" refString="Abdelsalam, K. M. (2018) First record of exotic Lysmatid shrimp Lysmata vittata (Stimpson, 1860) (Decapoda: Caridea: Lysmatidae) from the Egyptian Mediterranean coast. Mediterranean Marine Science, 19 (1), 124 - 131. https: // doi. org / 10.12681 / mms. 15591" type="journal article" year="2018">Abdelsalam 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Individuals from the Persian Gulf reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kemp, S." box="[432,582,474,501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="81 - 129" refId="ref20693" refString="Kemp, S. (1914) Notes on Crustacea Decapoda in the Indian Museum: V. Hippolytidae. Records of the Indian Museum, 10, 81 - 129." type="journal article" year="1914">Kemp (1914)</bibRefCitation>
possessed a longer rostrum, which exceeded the antennular peduncle, which suggests they may not reflect 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[488,590,511,536]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[488,590,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[628,712,510,536]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis box="[628,712,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stebbing" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[847,1014,510,536]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durbanensis">
<emphasis box="[847,1014,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. durbanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, reports of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1145,1247,511,536]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[1145,1247,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
around southern Africa, including 
<collectingRegion box="[350,511,546,572]" country="Mauritius" name="Cargados Carajos Shoals" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Saint Brandon</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[527,639,546,573]" name="Mauritius" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
) and the 
<collectingCountry box="[743,863,546,572]" name="Seychelles" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Borradaile, L. A." box="[878,1062,546,572]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="397 - 412" refId="ref18276" refString="Borradaile, L. A. (1917) The Percy Sladen Trust Expedition to the Indian Ocean in 1905, under the leadership of Mr. J. Stanley Gardiner, M. A. No. IX: On Carides from the Western Indian Ocean. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 17, 397 - 412." type="journal article" year="1917">Borradaile 1917</bibRefCitation>
) may not reflect 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1256,1358,547,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[1256,1358,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There is scant data for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[335,437,583,608]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[335,437,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from these regions and a directed collection effort and rigorous examinations are needed to establish the true identity of these shrimps.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1401]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">
<bibRefCitation author="Kemp, S." box="[199,350,654,681]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="81 - 129" refId="ref20693" refString="Kemp, S. (1914) Notes on Crustacea Decapoda in the Indian Museum: V. Hippolytidae. Records of the Indian Museum, 10, 81 - 129." type="journal article" year="1914">Kemp (1914)</bibRefCitation>
reported “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[471,573,655,680]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[471,573,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[803,861,654,680]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">India</collectingCountry>
and an unnamed variety of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1177,1280,655,680]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[1177,1280,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<specimenCount pageId="18" pageNumber="207" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
collected from the 
<collectingRegion box="[485,828,690,716]" country="India" name="Andaman and Nicobar Islands" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Andaman and Nicobar Islands</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[840,901,690,716]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">India</collectingCountry>
. The major difference between these forms was in the structure of the second pereopod, with 
<specimenCount box="[656,809,726,753]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of the unnamed 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1130,726,752]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" rank="variety" variety="with">variety with</taxonomicName>
28 carpal segments in both the left and right second pereopod and the other with 31 carpal segments in the left second pereopod (the right appendage was missing). Additionally, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kemp, S." box="[567,718,798,825]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="81 - 129" refId="ref20693" refString="Kemp, S. (1914) Notes on Crustacea Decapoda in the Indian Museum: V. Hippolytidae. Records of the Indian Museum, 10, 81 - 129." type="journal article" year="1914">Kemp (1914)</bibRefCitation>
noted “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[808,910,799,824]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[808,910,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1139,1197,798,824]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">India</collectingCountry>
possessed transverse bands on the pleon. Thus, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kemp, S." box="[447,616,834,860]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="81 - 129" refId="ref20693" refString="Kemp, S. (1914) Notes on Crustacea Decapoda in the Indian Museum: V. Hippolytidae. Records of the Indian Museum, 10, 81 - 129." type="journal article" year="1914">Kemp’s (1914)</bibRefCitation>
“ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[636,737,835,860]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[636,737,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is likely 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[854,937,834,860]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis box="[854,937,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while the unnamed variety is neither 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[246,330,870,896]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis box="[246,330,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="207" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1401]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">
Purported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[318,421,907,932]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[318,421,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with relatively high numbers of second pereopod segments have also been reported from the southern and central Indo-Pacific. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hale, H. M." box="[582,717,942,968]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="67 - 70" refId="ref20284" refString="Hale, H. M. (1929) Notes on the fauna of Dirk Hartog Island, Western Australia: No. 4. Crustacea. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia, 53, 67 - 70." type="journal article" year="1929">Hale (1929)</bibRefCitation>
noted “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[807,909,943,968]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[807,909,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from Dirk Hartog Island in western Australia possessed 23–24 meral segments of the second pereopod, which is considerably higher than reported in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1327,1430,979,1004]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[1327,1430,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,235,1014,1040]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis box="[151,235,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis box="[274,297,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L.</emphasis>
sp. AUS2 (8–13; table 2), and likely reflects another taxonomic entity. Similarly, 
<bibRefCitation author="Holthuis, L. B." box="[1219,1397,1014,1040]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref20449" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1947) The Decapoda of the Siboga Expedition: the Hippolytidae and Rhynchocinetidae. In: Weber, M. &amp; De Beaufort, L. F. (Eds.), The Decapoda of the Siboga Expedition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 1 - 100." type="book chapter" year="1947">Holthuis (1947)</bibRefCitation>
reported the number of second pereopod carpal segments of “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[829,931,1051,1076]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[829,931,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” collected from across 
<collectingCountry box="[1201,1313,1050,1076]" name="Indonesia" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, as well as New 
<collectingCountry box="[210,291,1086,1112]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Guinea</collectingCountry>
varied from 15–31. While some individuals in these collections may be 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[1092,1174,1086,1112]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis box="[1092,1174,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis box="[1210,1233,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L.</emphasis>
sp. AUS2, shrimp which possessed exceedingly high carpal segment counts (e.g.,&gt; 26) should be treated with caution, as they may be a different taxonomic entity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1401]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">
Interestingly, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kubo, I." box="[354,498,1194,1221]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="259 - 289" refId="ref21002" refString="Kubo, I. (1951) Some macrurous decapod Crustacea found in Japanese waters, with descriptions of four new species. Journal of the Tokyo University of Fisheries, 38, 259 - 289." type="journal article" year="1951">Kubo (1951)</bibRefCitation>
reported “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[620,722,1195,1220]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[620,722,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from 
<collectingCountry box="[804,868,1195,1221]" name="Japan" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Japan</collectingCountry>
that were similar in most respects to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1334,1437,1195,1220]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[1334,1437,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
examined in the present study, including in coloration pattern, except that individuals possessed a two-segmented accessory branch located at the forty-second segment of the dorsal antennule, a feature not reported by any member of the wider 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[292,393,1303,1328]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[292,393,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. Although we presume 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[759,860,1303,1328]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[759,860,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[974,1041,1303,1329]" name="Japan" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">Japan</collectingCountry>
, as indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayashi, K. I. &amp; Miyake, S." pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="121 - 163" refId="ref20326" refString="Hayashi, K. I. &amp; Miyake, S. (1968) Studies on the hippolytid shrimps from Japan: V. Hippolytid fauna of the sea around Amakusa Marine Biological Laboratory. Occasional Papers of Zoological Laboratory, 1, 121 - 163." type="journal article" year="1968">Hayashi &amp; Miyake (1968)</bibRefCitation>
, the “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[294,395,1339,1364]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[294,395,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="207">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kubo, I." box="[445,589,1338,1365]" pageId="18" pageNumber="207" pagination="259 - 289" refId="ref21002" refString="Kubo, I. (1951) Some macrurous decapod Crustacea found in Japanese waters, with descriptions of four new species. Journal of the Tokyo University of Fisheries, 38, 259 - 289." type="journal article" year="1951">Kubo (1951)</bibRefCitation>
is likely a different taxonomic entity or the description resulted from an error.
</paragraph>
